akka.stream.stage

Interface CallbackWrapper<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AsyncCallback<T>

    public interface CallbackWrapper<T>
extends AsyncCallback<T>
    INTERNAL API This trait wraps callback for GraphStage stage instances and handle gracefully cases when stage is not yet initialized or already finished.

    While GraphStage has not initialized it adds all requests to list. As soon as GraphStage is started it stops collecting requests (pointing to real callback function) and run all the callbacks from the list

    Supposed to be used by GraphStages that share call back to outer world
